description._content: Description: A close view of a girl wearing her dance ornaments. Her girdles consist of a double row of cowrie shells, many yards of braided human hair, ovulum ovum shells and a double row of flat coconut dises. Her plaque necklace is cut from conical shells. Location: Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Another set of ornaments showing necklaces of human teeth. Location: Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
